value.value: 肺静脈環流異常

abnormal development and attachment of the four pulmonary veins that normally attach to the left atrium of the heart, resulting in either partial or complete anomalous drainage back into the systemic venous circulation via an anomalous connection to the right atrium, the superior or inferior vena cava, the innominate vein, the coronary sinus or the left subclavian artery

definition.value: The word "anomalous" in this term and its children was used instead of abnormal since this is common usage among cardiologists.

value.value: 総肺静脈環流異常

abnormal development and attachment of all four pulmonary veins that normally attach to the left atrium of the heart, resulting in complete anomalous drainage back into the systemic venous circulation via an anomalous connection to the right atrium, the superior or inferior vena cava, the innominate vein, the coronary sinus or the left subclavian artery; in TAPVC, none of the four pulmonary veins are attached to the left atrium
部分肺静脈環流異常

abnormal development and attachment of one to three of the four pulmonary veins that normally attach to the left atrium of the heart, resulting in partial drainage back into the systemic venous circulation via an anomalous connection to the right atrium, the superior or inferior vena cava, the innominate vein, the coronary sinus or the left subclavian artery; in PAPVC, at least one pulmonary vein remains attached to the left atrium

label.value: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, intracardiac

value.value: 総肺静脈環流異常、心臓内型

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, intracardiac

value.value: the pulmonary veins connect directly to the right side of heart (eg, coronary sinus or directly to the right atrium) instead of the left atrium

label.value: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, infracardiac

value.value: 総肺静脈環流異常、下部心臓型

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, infracardiac

value.value: the common pulmonary vein travels down anterior to the esophagus through the diaphragm to connect to the portal venous system instead of the left atrium

label.value: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, mixed

value.value: 総肺静脈環流異常、混合型

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: total anomalous pulmonary venous connection, mixed

value.value: the right and left pulmonary veins drain to different sites other than the left atrium; for example, the left pulmonary veins into the left vertical vein to the left innominate, and/or the right pulmonary veins directly into the right atrium or coronary sinus
左心室形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the heart left ventricle, typically resulting in decreased size
左心室動脈瘤
thinning, stretching and bulging of a weakened heart left ventricular wall

label.value: heart left ventricle outflow tract stenosis

value.value: 左心室流出路狭窄

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: heart left ventricle outflow tract stenosis

value.value: abnormal narrowing or constriction of the portion of the left ventricle through which blood normally flows into the aorta

label.value: heart right ventricle outflow tract stenosis

value.value: 右心室流出路狭窄

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: heart right ventricle outflow tract stenosis

value.value: abnormal narrowing or constriction of part of the anteriosuperior, smooth-walled portion of the cavity of the right ventricle, beginning at the supraventricular crest and terminating in the pulmonary trunk
心房中隔動脈瘤
a saclike thinning, stretching and widening of the heart atrial septum resulting from weakening of the septum wall
腎毛細血管瘤
focal dilation of arteriocapillary junctions in the kidney
網膜毛細血管瘤
focal dilation of arteriocapillary junctions in the retina
冠状静脈形態異常
any structural anomaly of any of the veins that return blood from the heart muscles to the right atrium through the coronary sinus
総動脈幹中隔異常
anomaly in the process of dividing the common arterial trunk arising out of both heart ventricles to divide into the aorta and pulmonary artery during development
大動脈・肺動脈窓
a defect between the great vessels that results from failure of the conotruncal ridges to fuse resulting in an abnormal communication between the aorta and the pulmonary arteries
半総動脈幹症

congenital heart defect in which the origin of a pulmonary artery, usually the right, arises from the ascending aorta instead of the pulmonary trunk with the aortic and pulmonary valves remaining separate
肺動脈狭窄
abnormal narrowing or constriction of the pulmonary artery

definition.value: Do not confuse with pulmonary valve stenosis.

value.value: 肺動脈幹形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the pulmonary trunk, typically resulting in decreased size
弁上肺動脈狭窄
diffuse constriction or narrowing of the pulmonary trunk distal to the pulmonary valve
肺動脈形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the pulmonary artery, typically resulting in decreased size
肺動脈不連続
one or more pulmonary arteries is disconnected from the main pulmonary trunk and arises from a patent ductus arteriosus
肺動脈瘤
a protruding sac formed by the dilation of the wall of a pulmonary artery resulting from a weakening of the vessel wall
大動脈狭窄
diffuse constriction or narrowing of the aorta

definition.value: Do not confuse with aortic valve stenosis.

label.value: abnormal aortic arch and aortic arch branch attachment

value.value: 大動脈弓と大動脈弓分枝付着異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal aortic arch and aortic arch branch attachment

value.value: any anomaly of the connection site of the aortic branches to the aortic arch, including the attachment sites for the left common carotid artery, the left subclavian artery, and the brachiocephalic trunk which further splits to form the right subclavian artery and the right common carotid artery

label.value: aberrant origin of the right subclavian artery

value.value: 右鎖骨下動脈起始異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: aberrant origin of the right subclavian artery

value.value: the right subclavian artery arises from an atypical location on the aortic arch or the proximal descending aorta
血管輪
the trachea and esophagus are completely encircled by connected segments of the aortic arch and its branches
肺動脈スリング

anomalous origin of the left pulmonary artery from the posterior aspect of the right pulmonary artery, with the anomalous left pulmonary artery coursing over the right mainstem bronchus and then from right to left, posterior to the trachea or carina and anterior to the esophagus, to reach the hilum of the left lung, which compresses the lower trachea and right mainstem bronchus
胸部大動脈形態異常

any structural anomaly of the part of the aorta that extends from the origin at the heart to the diaphragm, and from which arises numerous branches that supply oxygenated blood to the chest cage and the organs within the chest
上行大動脈形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the ascending aorta, typically resulting in decreased size
上行大動脈拡張
the luminal space of the ascending aorta is increased in volume or area, usually with an increase of contained fluid
大動脈弁状部狭窄
a narrowing, diffuse constriction or obstruction of the ascending aorta located just distal to the aortic valve at the aortic root

label.value: abnormal ascending aorta and coronary artery attachment

value.value: 上行大動脈と冠状動脈付着異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal ascending aorta and coronary artery attachment

value.value: any anomaly of the connection site of any or all of the coronary arteries to the ascending aorta
下行大動脈拡張
widening or enlargment of the lumen of the descending aorta
下行大動脈形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the descending aorta, typically resulting in decreased size

label.value: anomalous pulmonary origin of left coronary artery

value.value: 左冠状動脈肺動脈異常起始

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: anomalous pulmonary origin of left coronary artery

value.value: the left coronary artery arises from the pulmonary artery insead of the aorta

definition.value: "anomalous" was used in the term name instead of "abnormal" due to common usage of this term among cardiologists.

value.value: 冠状動脈瘻

an abnormal communication between the terminus of a coronary artery, bypassing the myocardial capillary bed and entering either a chamber of the heart (coronary-cameral fistula) or any segment of the systemic or pulmonary circulation (coronary arteriovenous fistula)
冠状動脈瘤
a protruding sac formed by the dilation of the wall of a coronary artery resulting from a weakening of the vessel wall
頭蓋内動脈瘤
a protruding sac within the cranial space formed by the dilation of the wall of an artery or a vein resulting from a weakening of the vessel wall
脳動脈瘤
a protruding sac within the brain formed by the dilation of the wall of an artery or a vein resulting from a weakening of the vessel wall
肺動静脈奇形
abnormal communications between the pulmonary arteries and the pulmonary veins, or between a bronchial artery and the pulmonary vein

label.value: heart left ventricle to aorta tunnel

value.value: 左室から大動脈へのトンネル
an abnormal communication between the left ventricle and the ascending aorta in addition to the aortic valve
大動脈洞形態異常

any structural anomaly of the spaces betwen the superior aspect of each of the three cusps of the aortic valve and the dilated portion of the wall of the ascending aorta, immediately above each cusp; the three sinuses include the posterior (non-coronary sinus), and the right and left aortic sinuses (from which the left and right coronary arteries arise)
大動脈洞動脈瘤
a protruding sac formed by the dilation of the wall of the aortic sinus resulting from a weakening of the vessel wall
大動脈二尖弁
the presence of two cusps in the aortic valve instead of three
大動脈弓形成不全
decrease in the number of normal cells in normal arrangement in the aortic arch, typically resulting in decreased size
右鎖骨下動脈欠如
absence of one of the two subclavian arteries; the right subclavian artery normally extends from the brachiocephalic artery to the right side of the body
右鎖骨下動脈の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the artery that normally extends from the brachiocephalic artery to the right side of the body
左鎖骨下動脈の形態異常
any structural anomaly of the artery that extends from the aortic arch to the left side of the body

label.value: abnormal heart atrium auricular region morphology

value.value: 心房耳介部の形態異常

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: abnormal heart atrium auricular region morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the small conical pouch projections located on the upper anterior portion of each atrium of the heart
